{"word":"ἀγχίμολος","slug":"ἀγχίμολος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀγχίμολος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>μολεῖν</el>\n<p/><i>coming near</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b>: —in <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b> only in as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <i>near, close at hand</i>; so <el>ἐξ ἀγχιμόλοιο</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/>"}]}